race.comment: CALGA POWER (1) bolted in first-up from a long spell over this distance at Gosford. Has had his chance but just failed to measure up in two subsequent runs over longer trips. Freshened up and back to his pet distance so he looks perfectly placed to hit back. O'INVINCIBLE (2) raced handy and wouldn't lie down but found a couple a touch better when resuming over this distance at Canterbury last time out. Drawn to enjoy another nice run and with added fitness is a big chance to take this out. RASKOL (9) took a while to get clear then quickened nicely to collect her maiden win over 1200m at Canterbury recently. Surprising to see her coming back in distance but she will still play a big role. CAPTURE ME (8) led all the way and was highly impressive first-up at Gosford. Lightly raced and has stacks of upside. HAPPY BELLIE (4) returned from a long spell with a pleasing effort at Canterbury recently. No surprise to see her in the finish.
